   "body" : "As a consistency check, it is useful to see whether GBT clients are ready for segwit deployment before segwit is actually used on the network (and even before it activates).\r\n\r\nThe earlier behaviour only inserted a `default_witness_commitment` field in the GBT response whenever actual witness transactions were present. This PR changes it to do whenever 1) the GBT client claims to support segwit and 2) a segwit softfork is defined (which is effectively always in the current codebase, but may not be true for backports).",
